Project Steps: HorseVision AI – Image Classification System

Step 1: Data Collection

First, images were collected to create the dataset.
The images were divided into different categories (classes). For example:

Class 1: Horse images
Class 2: Other images

The purpose of collecting different classes is to teach the AI model how to distinguish between them.


Step 2: Training the Model Using Teachable Machine

Google Teachable Machine was used to train the image classification model.

The steps were:

Open Google Teachable Machine.
Select Image Project.
Create classes for the images.
Upload training images into each class.
Start the training process.

During training, the neural network learns the important features of each image, such as shapes, colors, and patterns.

Step 3: Exporting the Trained Model

After completing the training:

Click Export Model.
Choose TensorFlow/Keras model.
Download the model files.

The exported files include:

keras_model.h5 → contains the trained neural network.
labels.txt → contains the names of the classes.

Step 4: Setting Up the Environment

Google Colab was used as the programming environment.

The required libraries were installed:

TensorFlow
Keras
NumPy
Pillow

These libraries allow Python to load the model and process images.

